description:
Excellent Clash compilation, 1st of 3 CD box set. (CDs 2 and 3 below)
Mp3s 256 VBR

CD 1  - lots of tracks from eponymous 1st album and other early classics eg. 1977, Capital Radio One, City of the Dead, White Man In Hammersmith Palais

2 demos (Janie Jones, Career Opportunities)
2 lives (English Civil War, I Fought the Law)


Originally released in USA, then UK in 1991. Marked the beginning of the rehabilitation of the band. Came with a great booklet with terrific Pennie Smith photos and notes from the band, and also lyric book. Well worth looking for in 2nd hand shops etc if you\&amp;#039;re a big Clash fan or want to see where U2 nicked all their ideas from. I think a crappy smaller version in a CD sized box is also kicking around.

Enjoy and plant a tree for Joe.






